#AtHomeWithPlüsch / EPISODE 2 with @palakshah @ekayabanaras

Palak Shah knows her way around a saree. If anyone could make a case for incorporating them into wardrobes worldwide, it is her. The entrepreneur opened her custom-made @Schmalenbachdesign closet for Plüsch and gave us a glimpse into her enviable accessories collection, discussed her love for dancing and revealed her top recommendations for anyone travelling to Banaras.

Getting dressed for a family brunch, she talks us through her process of picking an outfit and looks every bit #AtHomeWithPlüsch.

Featuring: Palak Shah (@palakshah), CEO, Ekaya Banaras (@ekayabanaras) in a custom-made @pluschliving wardrobe

latestPosts.caption:
Ever since I was a child, my dad raised me telling me that I needed to be the next Indra Nooyi—not because of how famous she was, but because of how independent she was and how she made India proud. That’s something I’ve always aspired to be.

Being on the cover of a magazine has always been a dream, but never one that seemed achievable or even remotely possible because of the trade I was in. Saree shop owners were never considered brands—let alone allowed to sit at the same table as many business owners. So being on a list like @fortune.india 40 Under 40 obviously felt like a distant dream. And the cover? That felt completely out of the question. Why would they ever put me there? What had I really done? Back in the day, we weren’t even allowed to be at the same table as many designers.

But here we are—13 years of perseverance, of not giving up, of continuing to walk the road I set out on.
Mission: take Indian textiles global and make this industry the slickest, coolest, and most innovative one people have seen. And also—hey!—make the saree the next runway trend.

And trust me, that’s going to happen.
Don’t know when, but soon.

Next up: Ekaya New York. ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
For the longest time, I thought Banarasi was something you only wore on special occasions. Weddings, festivals, big days.

But somewhere along the way, I asked myself -  why should this kind of beauty only come out once in a while?

Why not every day?

That’s been my biggest goal with Ekaya - to reimagine Banarasi as something that’s not just timeless, but versatile. Pants, bags, scrunchies, even the smallest accessory can carry heritage forward.

Today, I’m wearing pants made by my sister Aarohi @arohiofficial__ , styled with a Prada blazer I picked up in @bicestervillage and @ysl boots and I’d wear this to any meeting, anywhere in the world.🤍
June 💌

No trip to Paris is complete without a day at @lavalleevillage by @thebicestercollection 💫
With its pastel-hued storefronts, cobblestone paths, and French countryside charm, it feels less like a shopping destination and more like a dreamy escape.

From luxury boutiques with irresistible offers to five-star services like personal shopping, valet, and hands-free shopping, La Vallée Village makes every visit feel special.

And don’t even get us started on the food! The Village’s Menu Palais is now helmed by a Three Michelin Star chef, come hungry, you’re in for a treat 🍴✨
